Nigerian Builders, Shelter Afrique in Project Talks, Punch Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-06-06T09:00:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-06/nigerian-builders-shelter-afrique-in-project-talks-punch-says.html
The Real Estate Developers
Association of  Nigeria  is in talks with Nairobi-based Shelter
Afrique about a $1 billion housing finance transaction, the
 Punch  newspaper reported, citing Olabode Afolayan, national
president of the body.  As part of the transaction, 12 developers will get $50
million each to construct 155,000 housing units for low- and
medium-income earners across the West African country, the
Lagos-based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburgt . 